      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Setbacks and encroachments are strictly regulated, and violating them can certainly lead to permit issues, regardless of the intended use. Building right up to a property line or encroaching onto the right-of-way usually constitutes a zoning violation and will likely cause the permit to be denied or require modifications. Even minor encroachments can be scrutinized, so it is crucial to ensure all construction adheres precisely to setback requirements before applying for your commercial shop permit.",
